\f0\b Keyboard shortcuts
\f1\b0 \
	When the iTunes window is frontmost, or you are in full-screen mode, some of the settings may be altered using a single letter keyboard shortcut. These are:\
\
	T - show track info. This turns on track info if it is off, then redisplays the current track info for 10 seconds.\
	P - toggle peak indicators on or off\
	L - flip left channel\
	R - flip right channel\
	V - toggle VU meters on or off (shows and hides them)\
	S - toggles between side-by-side and back-to-back layout\
	F - toggles between fixed size and fit-to-window\
	B - toggles the border on or off\
	N - toggles between linear and logarithmic modes\
	E - toggles between exponential and linear decay modes\
	< (,) - decrements number of frequency bands by one\
	> (.) - increments number of frequency bands by one\
	I - increase font size for track info (& redisplay it)\
	D - decrease font size for track info (& redisplay it)\
	A - toggles whether album info shown (& redisplay it)\
	M - toggles meter scales\
	X - turns on analogue VU meter layout (use S to change it back)\
\
\

\f0\b System requirements:\

\f1\b0 \
Any Macintosh running Mac OS X 10.3 (Panther) or later, and iTunes 3 or later. A speed of 600 MHz or better will give best results. Any G3, G4, G5 or Intel processor is fine. This version (2.0.6) is a Universal Binary and runs on all Intel-based Macs. The visualizer works with all version of iTunes from 3.0 onwards, including 7.0\
\
Note: When you run iTunes 7.0 with this plug-in for the first time after upgrading from an earlier version of iTunes, you may experience a crash. The problem should clear itself when you run iTunes again. If it does not, try discarding the preferences file.\
